+{"id":"frankenpandas-x8r65","title":"fd90.137: Merge-Asof recipe doesn't note merge_asof returns MergedDataFrame (not DataFrame)","description":"fd90.74-136 README audit. Merge-Asof for Time Series Alignment recipe at lines 1336-1342 binds the merge_asof result without noting that it's a MergedDataFrame, not a DataFrame:

  let result = merge_asof(&trades, &quotes, "timestamp", AsofDirection::Backward)?;

merge_asof returns Result<MergedDataFrame, JoinError>. MergedDataFrame is a struct with public 'index' and 'columns' fields but NO impl block — users can't call DataFrame methods on result directly. They need DataFrame::new(result.index, result.columns) to get a usable DataFrame.

The Merge: Advanced Options section already has this note (added in fd90.113). The Merge-Asof recipe doesn't. A user reading just the recipe and trying e.g. result.column("quote") would hit:
  error[E0599]: no method named 'column' found for struct 'MergedDataFrame'

Fix: add a parallel note immediately after the recipe explaining the MergedDataFrame return contract and the DataFrame::new conversion. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T12:49:07.384015866Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T12:50:21.097852443Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T12:50:21.094993870Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
